name: afqbtc
tweet: #Bitcoin is so divisible and this is vital for it to be practical and act as the medium of exchange for daily use.  Smaller fractions are crucial when it comes to paying transaction fees and completing micropayments.

name: afqbtc
tweet: The value of 1 Satoshi is always 100 millionth of a #Bitcoin and their values are tied together.  Each Bitcoin is divisible to eight decimal places, which means that you don't have to buy 1 full BTC.  You can acquire as low as 0.00000001 BTC or 1 Sat to be able to own Bitcoin.

name: afqbtc
tweet: #Bitcoin Sats  Satoshi/sat is the smallest unit of the Bitcoin, it is more or less to a Bitcoin what a penny is to a dollar.  $1 = 100 pennies, whereas 1 BTC = 100,000,000 Satoshis/Sats.  The unit has been named in collective homage to the creator of Bitcoin, Satoshi Nakamoto.
